## Environment Variables for ORMs

```bash
# .env — both connection strings needed for ORMs

# Transaction mode (port 6543) — used by app at runtime
DATABASE_URL="postgresql://postgres.[REF]:[PASSWORD]@aws-0-[REGION].pooler.supabase.com:6543/postgres"

# Direct connection (port 5432) — used by migrations and Prisma shadow DB
DIRECT_URL="postgresql://postgres:[PASSWORD]@db.[REF].supabase.co:5432/postgres"
```

---

## Drizzle vs Prisma — Quick Decision

Choose Drizzle when: you want minimal overhead, serverless-first design, schema as TypeScript, fastest cold starts.

Choose Prisma when: your team already knows Prisma, you want the Prisma Studio GUI, you need enterprise features like query engine extensions.

Both work correctly with Supabase RLS (when configured to use the right role). Both require port 6543 for production Netlify deployment.
